@@TJvFontComboBox
<TITLEIMG TJvFontComboBox>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Combos, JVCL.SelectAndChoose
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Combo box that enables the user to select a font from a drop-down list.
Description
  TJvFontCombobox is a TJvCustomComboBox descendant which enables the user to select a font from a
  drop-down list of the face names for all fonts supported by the screen /installed on the system.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.AddToMRU
Summary
  Adds the currently selected font to the MRU list.
Description
  Call AddToMRU to programmatically add the currently selected font to the MRU list. This method only
  has effect if foMRU is in Options.
Return value
  0 if the item was added (MRU items are always added at the top) or the index of an existing item in
  the MRU list.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.ClearMRU, TJvFontComboBox.MaxMRUCount, TJvFontComboBox.MRUCount,
  TJvFontComboBox.Options

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.ClearMRU
Summary
  Clears the MRU list.
Description
  Call ClearMRU to remove all fonts from the MRU list.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.AddToMRU

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.Device
Summary
  Specifies the device from which to retrieve the list of available fonts.
Description
  These are the possible values of Device:
  <TABLE>
    Value      Meaning
    ---------  ----------------------------------------------
    fdScreen   Retrieve from the screen.
    fdPrinter  Retrieve from the printer.
    fdBoth     Retrieve from both the screen and the printer.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.UseImages

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.DroppedDownWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width, in pixels, of the drop-down list.
Description
  Use DropDownWidth to customize the width of the drop-down list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.FontName
Summary
  Specifies the font name that is displayed in the edit box.
Description
  Use the FontName property to read the text of the combo box or specify a new \string for the FontName
  value, to change the current selected font name.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.FontSubstitute
Summary
  Returns a substitute font for a specific font.
Description
  Call FontSubstitute to retrieve the name of a substitute font for a font specified by parameter
  AFontName. This might be useful when a font is not installed on a system (for example, a font in a
  specific locale).
Parameters
  AFontName - The name of the font to search a substitute for.
Return value
  Returns the name of a substitute font, or the value of parameter AFontName if no substitute is
  found.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.FontName

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.HiliteColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteColor to read or change the background color of the text that is focused. The focused line
  is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.HiliteText

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.HiliteText
Summary
  Specifies the color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteText to specify the color of the text characters (as opposed to the background color) of
  the focused line. The focused text is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
See Also
  MaxMRUCount, HiliteColor

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.MaxMRUCount
Summary
  Specifies the max number of MRU items to display in the control.
Description
  Use MaxMRUCount to specify the max number of recently selected fonts at the top of the control.
  Setting MaxMRUCount to 0 (the default), means that the MRU list can contain any number of MRU items.
  To active the MRU list, include foMRU in Options. The MRu items are delimited by a double gray line
  beneath the last MRU item.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.AddToMRU, TJvFontComboBox.ClearMRU, TJvFontComboBox.MRUCount

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.MRUCount
Summary
  Specifies the number of MRU items in the control.
Description
  Use MRUCount to \read the number of items currently in the MRU list.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.AddToMRU, TJvFontComboBox.ClearMRU, TJvFontComboBox.MaxMRUCount

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.OnDrawPreviewEvent
Summary
  Occurs when the control is about to draw a font preview.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnDrawPreviewEvent to selectively supress drawing of the font preview in the
  control. OnDrawPreviewEvent is only called if foPreviewFont is in Options.
Parameters
  Sender       - The control that triggered the event.
  AFontName    - The name pf the fnt about to be drawn.
  APreviewText - The text to use to draw the preview.
  ATextWidth   - The approximate width required to draw the font name and the preview text.
  DrawPreview  - Indicates whether to draw th epreview or not for this font. The default value is
                  determined by comparing ATextWidth with ClientWidth.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.Options

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.Options
Summary
  Determines the appearance and behavior of the font combo box.
Description
  Use the Options property to customize the appearance and functionality of the combo box.

  Use Options to

  * Specify which type of fonts the combobox should contain.
  * Display each font name in the combo box using the specific font.
  * Display a font preview in the control.
  * Display a MRU list at the top of the control.
See Also
  TJvFontComboOptions

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.Sorted
Summary
  Determines whether the list portion of the combo box is alphabetized.
Description
  Set Sorted to true to sort the font names in the list alphabetically.

  When Sorted is changed from false to true, the original order of the items is lost. Setting Sorted
  back to false does not restore the original order.
Note
  If foMRU is in Options, Sorted is set to false and cannot be set to true.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.FontName, TJvFontComboBox.Options

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.UseImages
Summary
  Specifies whether to use images to indicate the font type.
Description
  If UseImages is set to True, the combobox uses images to indicate the font type. Set UseImages to
  False to disable showing images.

  The following table lists the possible images and their meaning.
  <TABLE>
    Image                      Font Type
    -------------------------  ----------------------------------------------------
    <IMAGE FontType_TrueType>  TrueType font.
    <IMAGE FontType_Printer>   The printer supports downloading this TrueType font.
    <IMAGE FontType_Fixed>     Other font, such as vector or raster fonts.
  </TABLE>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption
<TITLE TJvFontComboOption type>
Summary
  Defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a font combo box.
Description
  The \TJvFontComboOption type defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a font combo
  box.

  \TJvFontComboOptions is a set of TJvFontComboOption values.

  The following table lists the possible values:
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.Options

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foAnsiOnly
  Displays only fonts that use the Windows character set. Symbol fonts are not listed in the dialog.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foTrueTypeOnly
  Displays only TrueType fonts in the dialog. Other fonts are not listed.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foFixedPitchOnly
  Displays only monospaced fonts in the dialog. Proportionally spaced fonts are not listed, nor are
  TrueType fonts that do not have the fixed-pitch flag set in the style header.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foNoOEMFonts
  Removes OEM fonts from the combo box. Lists only non-OEM fonts.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foOEMFontsOnly
  Displays only OEM fonts in the combo box.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foScalableOnly
  Displays only scalable fonts in the combo box. Non-scalable (bitmap) fonts are removed from the
  list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foWysiWyg
  Displays each font name in the combo box using the specific font.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foDisableVerify
  Allows you to insert a font name that doesn't exists in the combo box's list.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foPreviewFont
  Displays a font preview in the control. If set, the font name is drawn using the controls font and a
  preview of the font is drawn using the string 'AbCdEfGhIj' right-aligned in the control. When this
  value is set, foWysiWyg is disabled.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption.foMRU
  Displays a MRU list of the last selected fonts at the top of the control. This value works in
  comjuction with the MaxMRUCount property. When this property is set, Sorted cannot be set to true.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOptions
<TITLE TJvFontComboOptions type>
<COMBINE TJvFontComboOption>

